      "writtenOn": "2020-04-27T17:29:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So as-is, onPrepare counts verbs, checks the path transformed size, etc. in order to make an educated choice about which geometry method to use. It looks kind of like:\n\n if (fullTriangulationIsWorthIt) {\n     prepeareNonOverlappingInnerTriangles();\n     prepareOuterCubics();\n     return;\n }\n\n if (middleOutIsWorthIt) {\n     prepareMiddleOutInnerTriangles();\n     prepareOuterCubics();\n     return;\n }\n\n prepareCubicWedges();\n\nSo at least for now my preference might be to leave it as-is. Both call sites for this method (onPrepare and the benchmark) fully expect it to use middle-out. onPrepare might be the more general method whose job is to make pixels happen without necessarily revealing too many implementation details. How strong of a preference is this for you?",
